<mg> is a unit:
    plural is <mg>

<kg> is a unit:
    plural is <kg>

<Test Unit> is a unit:
    plural is <Test Units>
    abbreviation is "tu"

<degree Celsius> is a unit:
    plural is <degrees Celsius>
    abbreviation is "°C"

<Temperature> is a number:
    valid values:
        35.0 <degrees Celsius> ... 42.0 <degrees Celsius>
    meaning:
        38.0 <degrees Celsius> ... 42.0 <degrees Celsius>:
            <High Fever> = "yes".
        35.0 <degrees Celsius> ... 37.9 <degrees Celsius>:
            <High Fever> = "no".
    question:
        ask "What is the patient's temperature?"

<High Fever> is an enumeration:
    valid values:
        "yes"; "no"

<Pain Level> is a number:
    question:
        style of question is <VisualAnalogScale>.
        question style is visual analogue scale:
            best value is 0.
            text for best value is "No Pain".
            worst value is 10.
            text for worst value is "Worst Pain".
    
<Aspirin> is a drug:
    ingredients:
        <Acetylsalicylic Acid> 500 <mg>
    dosage safety:
        maximum single dose = 1000 <mg>
        maximum daily dose = 4000 <mg>
        minimum time between doses = 4 hours
    administration:
        form of administration is "Tablet"
    interactions:
        assess interaction with <Warfarin>:
            show message "Warning: Risk of bleeding".

<Dr. House> is an addressee:
    contact information:
        email is "house@princeton-plainsboro.com"
        phone is "555-1234"
    after consent has been rejected:
         show message "Patient rejected consent.".

<Dr. Wilson> is an addressee:
    contact information:
        email is "wilson@princeton-plainsboro.com"

<OncologyTeam> is an addressee group:
    grouped addressees are <Dr. House>; <Dr. Wilson>
    order of contacting:
        contact all addressees in parallel

<Treatment Plan> is a plan:
    during plan:
        ask <Temperature>.
        <Temperature> = 37.0 <degrees Celsius>.
        
        assess <Temperature>:
            38.0 <degrees Celsius> ... 42.0 <degrees Celsius>:
                show message "Fever detected.".
                <High Fever> = "yes".
            35.0 <degrees Celsius> ... 37.9 <degrees Celsius>:
                show message "Normal temperature.".
                <High Fever> = "no".

        show message to <Dr. House> "Assessment complete.".
        send information "Temp Log" <Temperature>.

    every 1 day for 7 days:
        assess trend of <Temperature>:
            "increase":
                show message "Temperature is rising.".
            "decrease":
                show message "Temperature is falling.".
            "stable":
                show message "Temperature is stable.".

    change of <Pain Level>:
        context:
            timeframe: 24 hours ago
            data: <Pain Level>
        
        assess count of <Pain Level>:
            3 ... 100:
                show message "Pain recorded multiple times today.".
